N2  - The paper considers a class of optimization problems. The problems are linear programming problems: maximize cx subject to Ax = b with the additional constraint that x must also be an extreme point of a second convex polyhedron Dx = d, x ? 0. A cutting-plane algorithm for solving such problems is presented. Two numerical examples are also included.
